The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the seventh meeting of the National Space Council. Pence expressed excitement about the upcoming launch of American astronauts on American rockets from American soil, which is set to take place in one week. He praised the NASA team and expressed gratitude for their work in achieving President Trump's vision for renewed American leadership in space. Pence also highlighted the importance of this achievement during a time of great hope and encouragement as the country begins to reopen following the COVID-19 pandemic. The article also includes comments from NASA Administrator Jim Bridenstine and astronauts Colonel Robert Behnken and Colonel Douglas Hurley, who will be part of the upcoming mission. They discussed the progress of the Artemis program, which aims to return American astronauts to the Moon by 2024, and the preparations for the launch of the crew capsule to the International Space Station. Overall, the article emphasizes the significance of this mission in reaffirming American leadership in space.